# Exercise the LSP snippet completion accept path: seed an mnml-side
# snippet (via the snippet step), expand it, verify the placeholders
# Tab-cycle correctly. This is a proxy for the LSP path — the e2e
# harness doesn't connect to a real language server, but mnml's native
# snippet expansion uses the same `apply_snippet_edit` machinery.

snippet rs forr "for $1 in $2 {\n    $0\n}"

write code.rs ""
open code.rs

# Type the trigger, then expand.
type forr
command snippet.expand

# Expansion is on screen with `$1`/`$2`/`$0` stripped (rendered blank).
expect screen contains "for  in  {"

# 2026-07 CI-flake mitigation: add wait steps between edits so
# pending_tree_edits + snippet edits_consumed settle before the
# next key/type — matches the wait-step pattern in the
# snippet_backtab_visited.test companion. Without these the
# macOS CI runner's 50ms render sleep can drift past the 120ms
# highlights-idle gate and land in an edge case where the next
# type misses its stop-shift.

# Cursor is at $1. Type the loop variable.
wait 150
type i

# Tab moves to $2 — type the iterable.
wait 150
key tab
wait 150
type items

# Tab again moves to $0 (the body indent).
wait 150
key tab
wait 150
type println

# Final state shows the filled-in template.
expect screen contains "for i in items {"
expect screen contains "println"
expect dirty true
